Swatch’s Tissot Aims to Double Production, Le Temps Reports

-- B y   T o m   M u l i e r
-- 
2011-03-17T07:42:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/swatch-s-tissot-aims-to-double-production-le-temps-reports.html
  Swatch Group AG (UHR) ’s Tissot brand aims
to double its production to as many as 6 million watches a year
and is investing 20 million Swiss francs ($22 million) in a
logistics center to boost capacity,  Le Temps  said, citing
Francois Thiebaud, president of the brand.  Tissot’s sales rose more than 20 percent in the first two
months of the year, Thiebaud was cited by the newspaper as
saying. The brand expects to sell 3.5 million to 4 million
watches this year, he also said, according to Le Temps. The
newspaper didn’t give a timeframe for doubling production.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tom Mulier in Geneva at 
 tmulier@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at   cperri@bloomberg.net . 